      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "```python\ndef kalman_filter(data):\n    # Kalman filter implementation\n    # This is a simplified version and may not be optimal for all cases\n    # Initialize variables\n    x = 0.0  # estimate of the true value\n    P = 1.0  # estimate uncertainty\n    Q = 1e-5  # process noise covariance\n    R = 0.1  # measurement noise covariance\n    K = 0.0  # kalman gain\n\n    filtered_data = []\n\n    for z in data:\n        # Prediction update\n        x = x\n        P = P + Q\n\n        # Measurement update\n        K = P / (P + R)\n        x = x + K * (z - x)\n        P = (1 - K) * P\n\n        filtered_data.append(x)\n\n    return filtered_data\n\ntest_kalman()\n```\n\nThis should make the `test_kalman` pass. The Kalman filter is a bit simplified here, but it should give you a reasonable smoothing effect on the noisy GPS data. The constants `Q` and `R` can be adjusted based on your specific sensor characteristics for better results.",
